6b-4:
-------------------------
Added the ALL_STATIC alias for JPEG_STATIC

As of 6b-3, the dll is named "cygjpeg6b.dll" NOT "libjpeg.dll".  This 
  helps to avoid dll naming conflicts between cygwin dll's and 
  dlls from other platforms (native, pw, etc).  If you have an
  executable that depends on "libjpeg.dll" you may either recompile 
  your app so that it links with libjpeg.dll.a/cygjpeg6b.dll, or install
  *just* the dll from jpeg-6b-2.tar.gz into your /usr/bin 
  directory.

The dll is VERSIONED. (i.e. "cygjpeg6b.dll" NOT "cygjpeg.dll") because
  there are rumors that libjpeg-6c is on its way out.  Worse, the
  API between minor releases (e.g. 6a to 6b) changed, so I imagine
  it will change again between 6b and 6c.   To enable the upcoming
  version and this one to coexist, the dll's are versioned.
  (Versioning is not necessary for static libs until AFTER the
  release of an incompatible library, but you've got to think ahead
  for the dynamic libs). 

Since the ABI/API changes between even minor release for libjpeg,
  we must use the entire "6b" string as the version tag, instead 
  of just "6".

